A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating and commending Caterpillar Inc. on its 100th anniversary; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, this year, Caterpillar Inc. celebrates a century of industry leadership, innovation,
4 excellence, and remarkable contributions to infrastructure, manufacturing, and technological
5 advancement; and
6 WHEREAS, founded on April 15, 1925, Caterpillar Inc. originated from the pioneering work
7 of Benjamin Holt and C.L. Best, whose vision revolutionized track-type tractor technology
8 and laid the foundation for one of the most recognizable brands in heavy equipment; and
9 WHEREAS, Caterpillar Inc. has grown from its humble beginnings into a global leader in
10 manufacturing construction and mining equipment, off-highway diesel and natural gas
11 engines, industrial gas turbines, and diesel-electric locomotives, with operations spanning
12 countless industries and markets worldwide; and
13 WHEREAS, the company has maintained a significant presence in the United States,
14 including its headquarters in Irving, Texas, and multiple facilities across Georgia that support
15 jobs in Griffin, Atlanta, Athens, and Patterson; and
